1) Quick overview (the short story)

Jenkins is an open-source automation server used for CI/CD — it runs jobs (freestyle or pipelines), 
Can use agents/nodes to run builds, stores configuration in JENKINS_HOME, and supports “Pipeline as code” using a Jenkinsfile.

2) How to install (two fast, common ways)

A —Run Jenkins quickly with Docker (recommended for learning):

  # create persistent volume
  docker volume create jenkins_home

  # run Jenkins LTS (HTTP 8080, agent 50000)
  docker run -d --name jenkins \
  -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 \
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts

  #To get the initial admin password (needed for setup wizard):
  docker exec jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword

B — Install on Ubuntu / Debian (systemd):
(Install Java first, add Jenkins repo, then install.)
  $ sudo apt update
  $ sudo apt install -y openjdk-17-jdk   # or java 11/17 depending on Jenkins requirements

# add Jenkins repo + key (follow official instructions)
  $ curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee \
  /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins.gpg > /dev/null
  echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins.gpg] https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/" \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list
  $ sudo apt update
  $ sudo apt install -y jenkins
  $ sudo systemctl enable --now jenkins
# initial password for apt install:
  $ sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword

# Official install docs & guides.
  https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/?utm_source=chatgpt.com

3) First run: setup wizard (what to do)

Open http://<server-ip>:8080.

Enter the initial admin password (from the file above).

Choose 'Install suggested plugins' (recommended for learning) or select them manually.

Create your first admin user?
This is covered in the install docs and Docker notes.
https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/

4)OPTIONAL # Run Jenkins with Docker socket and bind Docker CLI (host path may vary) allows Jenkins to call docker binary.

# create persistent volume if not created
docker volume create jenkins_home

# Run Jenkins with docker socket and bind docker CLI
docker run -d --name jenkins \
  -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000 \
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
  -v /usr/bin/docker:/usr/bin/docker \   # optional; allows Jenkins to call docker binary
  jenkins/jenkins:lts

# Run an SSH-enabled Jenkins agent container:
docker run -d --rm --name=agent1 --network jenkins -p 2222:22 -e JENKINS_AGENT_SSH_PUBKEY=[public-key] jenkins/ssh-agent:jdk21.

Copy the agent's public SSH key to Jenkins.
Go to "Manage Jenkins" → "Nodes" → "New Node" and set up this agent with the agent's SSH configuration.



